  "texts": [
    "In this paper, we have established a race between classical and quantum generative models in terms of quality-based generalization and defined four types of practical quantum advantage (PQA).",
    "Here, we focus on what we referred to as potential PQA (PPQA), which aims to compare quantum models with the best-known classical algorithms to the best of our efforts and compute capabilities for the specific task at hand.",
    "We have proposed two different competition rules for comparing different models and defining PPQA.",
    "We denote these rules as tracks based on the race analogy.",
    "We have used QCBMs, RNNs, TFs, VAEs, and WGANs to provide an instance of this comparison on the two tracks."
  ],
